@model Experiment
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" media="screen" href="~/css/Idea/Experiment.css"/>
</head>
<header> 
        <partial name="HeadingPartial"/>
</header>
<body>

    <nav>
        <a href="/dashboard">Home |</a>
        <a href="/Edit">Edit User Profile |</a>
        <a href="/NewIdea">New Idea |</a>
        <a href="/AllIdeas">Ideas in your que |</a>
        <a href="/review">Review ideas |</a>
        <a href="/Logout">Logout</a>
    </nav>


    <div class="MainText"> 
    <h4>Experiment-Driven Design</h4>
    A thought process to help you figure out how to get implement your ideas!
    Each Experiment you conduct will have three parts.
    One, Describe your Experiments, provide your hypothesis and predictions.
    Two, Describe your result, show whether the experiments worked and your beliefs about them.
    Three, give each experiment a score based on how successful it was in 
    proving that your idea will accomplish the desired results.
    <br>Tips:<br>
    -Make your experiments easy to follow so the next person approving your idea will understand it better.<br>
    -Try to be specific in your experiments. And clarify proof-of-concept.<br>
    -Take your time. All your progress will be saved so come back and add more experiments.
    </div>

    <div class="EddPic">

        <img src="~/images/EddPic.png">

    </div>
    <br>
    <h3>Submit an Experiment</h3>
    <form asp-action="addexperiment/@ViewBag.id" asp-controller="Idea" method="post">
        <br>
        <input type="hidden" asp-for="IdeaId" value=id>

    <span asp-validation-for="ExperimentDesc"></span>
        <label asp-for="ExperimentDesc"></label>
        <textarea asp-for="ExperimentDesc"></textarea>

        <span asp-validation-for="Result"></span>
        <label asp-for="Result"></label>
        <input asp-for="Result">

        <span asp-validation-for="Score"></span>
        <label asp-for="Score"></label>
        <input asp-for="Score">
        <br>
        <button>Submit</button>

    </form>

   <h3>Completed Experiments</h3>

<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Experiment</th>
    <th>Result</th>
    <th>Score</th>
  </tr>
      @foreach(var e in ViewBag.Experiment)
      {
  <tr>
    <td>@e.ExperimentDesc</td>
    <td>@e.Result</td>
    <td>@e.Score</td>
  </tr>
      }
</table>





</body>